<P>A SERMON, On 1 CHRONICLES xxix. 28. Occa&s;ioned by the DEATH of KING <HI>GEORGE</HI> the SECOND, Of happy Memory, who departed this Life on the 25th Day of OCTOBER, in the Year of our LORD, 1760, in the 77th Year of his Age, and the 34th of his Reign; beloved and honored by his Subjects, for his Eminent-Royal-Virtues.</P>
<P>TOGETHER, With &s;ome brief Hints, of the amiable CHARACTER of His Maje&s;ty KING <HI>GEORGE</HI> the THIRD, Now &s;eated on the Briti&s;h THRONE, and the au&s;picious OMENS, that attend his Infant REIGN.</P>
<P>PREACHED At PHILADELPHIA, JANUARY 25th, 1761, and publi&s;hed at the reque&s;t of the Audience.</P>
<P>By GILBERT TENNENT, Mini&s;ter of the Go&s;pel of CHRIST.</P>
<Q><BIBL><HI>PSALM cxlvi. 3, 4.</HI></BIBL>
<P>Put not your Tru&s;t in Princes, nor in the Son of Man, in whom there is no Help: His Breath goeth forth, he returneth to his Earth; in that very Day his Thoughts peri&s;h.</P></Q>
<Q><L>Pallida Mors,</L>
<L>Aequo pul&s;at Pede, pauperum Tabernas, Regumque Turres.</L></Q>
<Q><BIBL><HI>2 CHRONICLES i. 11, 12.</HI></BIBL>
<P>And God &s;aid unto <HI>Solomon</HI>&mdash;Wi&s;dom and Knowledge is granted unto thee.&mdash; <HI>2 Kings xxiii. 3.</HI> And the King made a Covenant to walk after the Lord, and keep his Statutes with all their Heart.&mdash;</P></Q>
<Q><L>"Ad exemplum Regis, totus formatur orbis.</L>
<L>"Tu regere imperio, populos Brittane memento:</L>
<L>"Haec tibi erunt artes; paci&s;que impo nere morem,</L>
<L>"Parcerc Subjectis, et debellare Superbos.</L></Q>
<P>PHILADELPHIA: Printed by W. DUNLAP, MDCCLXI.</P>
